subSubSection.paragraph:
Structure
. Antennal segment I slightly narrower basally with a row of long and erect setae ventrally. Antennal segments II and III each with a small tuft of short, erect setae apically. Rostrum reaching anterior margin of mesoesternum. Pronotum enclosed by posterolateral angles of eye and medioanterior angles of mesonotum. Mesonotum with a median longitudinal suture. Mesoacetabulum in ventral view with a short tooth-shaped projection (
Fig. 2b
). Mesosternum with a median longitudinal suture. Metanotum with posterior margin sinuous. Fore femur with an irregular row of long, thin setae on anteroventral surface. Fore tibia with a row of short, erect setae on the lateral margin, and with a triangular apical projection. Mediotergite I as long as metanotum. Mediotergite VIII longer than wide, twice as long as mediotergite VII and rounded apically. Paramere arcuate and broadly widened medially; apex with dorsal margin curved and ending straight, and ventral margin straight (
Fig. 3b
). Vesica sclerites: auxiliary basal sclerite narrowed medially (
Fig. 4c, d
), dorsal sclerite long and angled downwards anteriorly (
Fig. 4d
). Lateral sclerite reduced at base and widened medially, with distal region truncated and directed towards the center in dorsal view and with a short cleft in lateral view (
Fig. 4d
).
